'''Sir John Macdonell''' [[Order of the Bath|KCB]], [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (1 August 1846 &ndash; 17 March 1921) was a British jurist. He was [[Queen's Remembrancer|King's Remembrancer]] (1912–1920) and ainvested as a Knight Commander of the [[Order of the Bath]].<ref>Fillebrown, Charles Bowdoin. ''The Principles of Natural Taxation''. Chicago: A. C. McClurg & co., 1917. [https://books.google.com/books?id=hB9NAAAAIAAJ&printsec=titlepage&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0#PPA23,M1 Page 23].</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=MACDONELL, Sir John|magazine=Who's Who|year=1907|volume= 59|page=1117|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yEcuAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA1117}}</ref> [[Thomas Shaw, 1st Baron Craigmyle|Shaw of Dunfermline]] gives a prefatory biography in ''Historical Trials''.

